  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Strikes in the Soviet Union by thousands of coal miners and other workers have shut down more than 200 mines and factories in the country's two top coal-producing regions:
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   the Donetsk region of the Ukraine and Siberia's Kuzretsk Basin.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The miners are demanding more local control over their industry, higher wages, and better living conditions.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Government negotiations have resolved most of the demands, including those on pensions and overtime,
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   but some longer-term questions will take up to a month to settle and miners are refusing any delay.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   A law on ending strikes and labor conflicts is being rushed through the Supreme Soviet.
  </a>
